review_text:
1. The queue for each ride averages at 50 minutes each (we only chose to ride for kid’s ride above 110 cm for our 5-years old son). Not much my family and I can play from 10 am to 6 pm. Perhaps due to many rides that are unavailable, hence the Park management may consider to make available and open all other rides soonest to reduce waiting time in average (too congested);
2. Should add more chairs around the park;
3. Limited number of cafe and stall that sell food that opens;
4. Even the restaurants are not in proper condition and is too crowded. Need to open more restaurant to distribute the crowds;
5. The toilets are filthy and not well taken care of;
6. People are skipping queues especially at the Planet of The Apes ride;
7. The VQ is confusing as no clear instruction of how to use them;
8. Bring back the Express Pass. More straightforward than the VQ;
9. Train your staff better. Lots of staff seems unprofessional as they were having conversation among them in front of the customers who are queueing. Many are also rough with their voice tone like shouting when giving instruction to move forward and appeared to be generally unfriendly (no smiles nor greetings at all);
10. Your apps accuracy is high, however, with standard errors about 5 to 10 minutes;
11. The timing for operation may be considered to be extended, such that to open much earlier at 9:00 am and to closes much later at 8:00 pm. Given the average high waiting time, 8 hours passes very fast (rest, meals in between, prayers, toilet break etc.)
12. Outdoor park ticket price is a bonus. Please keep the price relatively affordable so that many Malaysian can afford to attend the Theme Park.
